<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT January 8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Lebanese President Elias Hrawi has pledged again
that the Lebanese army will guarantee security on the border with
Israel after Israeli troops withdraw from south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
In his remarks published in Beirut's conservative An-Nahar
daily Wednesday, Hrawi repeated a demand for the implementation of
U.N. Security Council Resolution 425, which calls for an
unconditional Israeli withdrawal from south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian and Turkish security officials started their
first round of security talks focusing on the current sensitive
and complicated issues, local media reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- Six people were killed and seven others injured
in a bus-tractor collision in India's Uttar Pradesh last night,
the Press Trust of India said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Police said that all the victims were travelling in a trolley
attached to the tractor when the accident occurred.
</P>
<P>
KAMPALA -- Joseph Kony, leader of the rebel Lord's Resistance
Army (LRA), has penetrated last Sunday into northern Uganda from
Sudan, to which he fled last August when the battle between IRA
and the government troops was at its climax, a report reaching
here said Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
