<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ANC Celebrates 85th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The African National
Congress (ANC) of South Africa today celebrated its 85th
anniversary at its headquarters here, calling on all its members to
consolidate the national democratic revolution.
</P>
<P>
In a summary of the January 8 statement entitled "1997 -- A
Year for Reaffirming the ANC cadre", ANC's Deputy
Secretary-General Cheryl Carolus said that the party will
collectively rededicate itself to building an ANC cadreship to
carry forward the vasting transformation process starting after
the 1994 general elections.
</P>
<P>
The summary focused on calls to various sectors within the ANC
and the nation to dedicate themselves to rebuilding the economy,
deepening productivity, and enhancing their own skills.
</P>
<P>
President Nelson Mandela, as usual, will deliver the full
anniversary speech at a national rally in Free State Province on
January 12, said Carolus.
</P>
<P>
The ANC, established in 1912 and banned most of the time
during the apartheid era, was the biggest black political party
in South Africa before coming into power in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
