<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arms Exports Rise in Sweden </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's arms exports rose by
65 percent in the first nine months of 1996 over the same
period of the previous year, local press reported here today.
</P>
<P>
The total value of exports of arms and ammunition during the
period amounted to 1096 million Swedish kronors (about 170 million
U.S.dollars).
</P>
<P>
These figures are based on a survey made by the Swedish Peace
and Arbitration Association which is in turn based on data
provided by Statistics Sweden.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan, Venezuela, Indonesia and Brazil are among the ten
largest purchasers of Swedish arms last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
