<HEADLINE> Canada's Bombardier Wins Record Sale Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Canadian plane maker Bombardier
Inc. has won the largest single aircraft sale to build 30 Canadair
regional jets for the U.S. based Atlantic Southeast Airlines.
</P>
<P>
Atlantic Southeast has placed firm orders for the jets and has
options on 60 more, reports said today.
</P>
<P>
"It's a major, major order," said Bombardier spokesman Colin
Fisher, adding that the deal should be concluded within weeks.
</P>
<P>
Delivery of the 50-seat regional jet will start in August and
continue at a rate of one a month.
</P>
<P>
The 30 firm orders and spare parts for the aircraft are worth
600 million U.S. dollars to Bombardier. If all options are
exercised, the value of the contract could rise to 1.8 billion
dollars, reports said.
</P>
<P>
The sale would tighten Bomdardier's grip on the growing
regional aircraft market, analysts said.
</P>
<P>
The company's share of that worldwide market rose to 45 percent
last year from 27 percent in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
