<HEADLINE> Rockets Flys High in China Basketball 1st Division </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion August First
Rockets glided past the Shanghai Oriental 75-61 to snap the hosts'
winning streak of nine straight wins on Wednesday at the Chinese
basketball first division league.
</P>
<P>
The Rocket remained on top of the 12-team standing with a
win-loss record of 11-1 while the Oriental dropped to the third
from the second in 9-3 after 12 round matches.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning Hunters clambered to the second place with a 10-2 mark
after outshooting the Lianhang Eagles 95-73.
</P>
<P>
Gong Xiaobin scored a round high 36 points to give the Shandong
Flaming Bulls a 78-68 win over hosts Shenyang Lions. The two sides
tied at 40-all at the end of the first half.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan Pandas played a tough defensive game to upset Guangdong
Tigers 75-67. The Pandas held the Tigers scoreless for four
minutes in the beginning of the second half to overcome a 40-34
deficit at the interval.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Ducks hit nine three-pointers but still went down to
Jiangsu Nangang, who were led by the league's MVP Hu Weidong with
22 points, seven rebounds and eight assists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
