dollar deal signed in Moscow last Saturday had also been conveyed
to Greece's ambassador in the U.S. Lucas Tsila.
</P>
<P>
Asked about the State Department's official representative for
Southern Europe Carey Cavanaugh's visit to the region this
weekend, covering Nicosia, Athens and Ankara, Reppas replied that
the government had not been informed about the issues which the
U.S. envoy intends to raise.
</P>
<P>
Reppas said that the procurement of the S-300 system could be
canceled "tomorrow" if a program was implemented immediately
for the total demilitarization of the island. 
</P>
