<HEADLINE> Nigerian Police Intensifies Security Measures in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Police in Lagos, the largest city
of Nigeria, has intensified security measures after a bomb
exploded on Tuesday in an army bus killing one and injured 29
others.
</P>
<P>
The Lagos State Commissioner of Police, Alhaji Abubakar, told
a news conference today that the police patrol teams will have more
searches on the street and more policemen will be deployed.
</P>
<P>
No arrests have been made since Tuesday's explosion, which is
the third in three weeks in the former capital of Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
The first one on December 16 seriously damaged a car in the
convoy of Lagos State Administrator Colonel Muhammed Marwa. Marwa
was not hurt but two security guards in the car were injured.
</P>
<P>
The second explosion two days later left 18 officials of the
state environmental task force in a bus injured.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar called on citizens to cooperate and report any
suspectible activities. 
