<DOCNO> XIE19970109.0046 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Katyusha Attacks Northern Israel Amid High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Tension escalated in south
Lebanon tonight following a spate of exchanging fire between
Israeli occupation forces and the Lebanese guerrillas of the
pro-Iranian Hezbollah, or Party of God, in the border area.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here quoted security sources said in south
Lebanon that several Katyusha rockets were fired into the western
Galilee in northern Israel tonight, and no word on casualties was
available.
</P>
<P>
The same sources said that another 12 Katyusha rockets landed
on the outskirts of Markaba village only 200 meters away from the
Lebanese-Israeli border, claiming that no casualties were caused.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah denied any link with the attack, and no group in
Lebanon has claimed responsibility for the Katyusha attacks.
</P>
<P>
The Shiite fundamentalist Hezbollah used to fire Katyusha
rockets, the most advanced of which has a range of 40 kilometers,
usually when south Lebanese civilians were killed or wounded by
Israeli forces.
</P>
<P>
But a cease-fire understanding brokered by the United States
and France between Lebanon and the Jewishs state in April barred
the guerrilla group from using the weapon, supposedly provided
by Iran.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued in Beirut tonight, the Islamic
Resistance, the military wing of Hezbollah, announced it thwarted
an infiltrating attempt of an Israeli commandos force late this
afternoon into a Hezbollah-controlled area at the Litani river
basin, killing and wounding several Israelis.
</P>
<P>
Later, the Israelis fired heavy artilleries at the Litani river
basin as well as vicinities of south Lebanese villages in the
nearby areas, security sources said.
</P>
<P>
This was the second Israeli bombing today. In retaliation for
a dawn bombing attack on an Israeli patrol, Israeli artillery
fired more than 150 shells at Hezbollah targets in Iglim Al-Toffah
and Western Beqaa since this morning without causing casualties,
according to Police sources in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The Islamic Resistance, the military wing of Hezbollah,
announced that five Israeli soldiers were injured in a mine
explosion early this morning in the eastern sector of the Israeli
self-proclaimed buffer zone.
</P>
<P>
Today's escalation in south Lebanon came just as the
five-nation committee monitoring a limited truce on the
Lebanese-Israeli border wound up this morning its first meeting
in 1997.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued at the end of a two-day meeting, the
committee urged the Israeli forces and Lebanese guerrillas to
prevent civilians from being hurt in military operations.
</P>
<P>
The committee comprising France, the United States, Syria,
Lebanon and Israel was established under a cease-fire
understanding brokered by the U.S. and France last April, which
put an end to a 17-day Israeli blitz in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Israel established the 1,100-square-kilometer "security zone"
in 1985 in a bid to protect northern Israel from crossing-border
attacks by Lebanese guerrillas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
