<HEADLINE> Opposition UNITA Deputies to Arrive in Luanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Deputies of the opposition
National Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA) will
arrive here on Friday to attend the Angolan National Assembly,
Second Deputy Speaker Jaime Chinguimbo said today.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he denied an earlier claim by UN envoy to Angola
Blondin Beye that the UNITA deputies will arrive next Friday.
</P>
<P>
The assembly has created all necessary conditions for the
return of the UNITA deputies, said Chinguimbo.
</P>
<P>
UNITA deputies and members of the future government of
national unity and reconciliation will be arranged in four
high-graded hotels in the capital at the beginning, he said.
</P>
<P>
UNITA, the largest opposition party in the southern African
country, won 70 of all the 223 seats in the assembly in Angola's
first multi-parties elections held in September, 1992.
</P>
<P>
However, only seven UNITA deputies so far have inaugurated due
to the outbreaking of civil war. 
</P>
