<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing to Simplify Check-Ups on Overseas-Funded Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital will greatly
simplify the procedure of its regular annual check-ups on
overseas-funded enterprises, in response to a central government
decree on the issue to improve the local investment environment.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made by Vice-Mayor Lu Yucheng at today's
opening of a local conference on the issue held by the municipal
government.
</P>
<P>
Beginning this year, the city's yearly reviews on capital,
operation, accounting, foreign exchange and import and export for
these firms will be jointly conducted by seven local authoritative
departments, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
Of these, only the industrial and commercial administration has
the right to charge for the annual examination, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The time, site, procedure and charges related to the joint
yearly examination will be unified. It will be conducted from
January 15-April 30 every year, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
