<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kohl Optimistic About NATO's Eastward Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Germany Chancellor Helmut Kohl said
today that he was optimistic about the eastwards expansion of the
North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO).
</P>
<P>
Kohl told a news conference here that he believed NATO could
reach consensus with Russia and Ukraine on this issue.
</P>
<P>
He said a "new boundary maker" should not be created again
between NATO and Russia following the cold war era.
</P>
<P>
Kohl said that he believed with reason that the two sides could
reach rational compromise through joint efforts.
</P>
<P>
He could understand Russia's misgivings, as well as Russia's
hope of receiving interest compensation.
</P>
<P>
But when holding talks with Russian President Boris Yeltsin
last week in Moscow, Kohl stressed again that nobody could veto
NATO's eastwards expansion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
