<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Industrial Output up 13 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- China's industrial output in
1996 increased by 13.1 percent to reach 1,906 billion yuan,
according to a report released today by the State Statistics
Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The report noted that the nation's industry enjoyed stable
growth rates in the past four quarters at 13.6 percent, 13.1
percent, 11.8 percent and 15.7 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Non-state industries registered higher growth rates than that
of the state-owned sector.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the value-added output by the state
enterprises saw a growth rate of 6.7 percent, while that of the
collective operations increased by 17.7 percent, and that of
other economic sectors went up 13.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Last year China's light and heavy industries basically
developed at the same pace, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The light industrial growth rate was 13.5 percent, 0.8
percentage points higher than that of heavy industry's 12.7
percent.
</P>
<P>
The gap was much lower than 1994's 3.1 percentage points and
1995's 4.5 percentage points.
</P>
<P>
In 1996 production of most of industrial products was carried
out in line with market demand, said the report, adding that the
output of energy products and raw material products enjoyed a stable
increase.
</P>
<P>
The output of primary energy in the country last year reached
1.26 billion tons of standard coal, up 6.4 percent over the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
The bureau said that China's sales rate against industrial
production was 95.86 percent in the whole year. The figure in the
fourth quarter was 98.9 percent, progressively increasing from the
first quarter's 93 percent.
</P>
<P>
Yet, the bureau noted, the national industry's economic
efficiency was still low, especially in state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
It urged governments at all levels to take effective measures to
help solve the economic difficulties facing those enterprises in
1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
