<HEADLINE> Scientist Awarded for Study of Landslides </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Wang Gongxian, a scientist of
the Ministry of Railways, was presented the "Mao Yisheng Mechanics
and Basic Engineering Award" here today for his pioneering
research in the treatment of landslides.
</P>
<P>
Receiving the award with Wang were 72 other people, including
researchers, university students, middle school students and
primary school teachers who have made outstanding contribution to
the civil engineering science.
</P>
<P>
The honor was established in 1991 by the Mao Yisheng Science
and Technology Fund to commemorate Mao Yisheng, the late bridge
expert and the founder of China's modern civil engineering
science.
</P>
<P>
In the past six years, the award has been given to 295 people
who made outstanding contributions in science and technology and
education. 
</P>
</TEXT>
