<DOCNO> XIE19970109.0065 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Asks Italy to Return Historical Relic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian government
today decided to send a delegation to Italy in a few weeks in an
effort to speed up the return of the Axum Obelisk looted by
Italians during colonial time.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made at a high-level meeting of the "Return
Our Obelisk" Committee established by the concerned government
departments and well-known personalities in Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
After listening to a report on technical and legal
preparations over the issue in the past few months, the meeting
decided to send a delegation to Italy to discuss with Italian
officials on matters relating to the return of the obelisk to its
original place.
</P>
<P>
Technical experts in the delegation are expected to carry out
detailed consultations on the removal and transport of the
obelisk with their Italian counterparts.
</P>
<P>
The meeting recalled that the Axum Obelisk now in Rome was
looted on the express orders of Benito Mussolini, the leader of
facist Italy 60 years ago in 1937.
</P>
<P>
"Although it was agreed in the peace treaty in 1947 and in the
Ethio-Italy agreement of 1956 to return the obelisk to Ethiopia,
Italy has not complied with the agreements," the meeting pointed
out.
</P>
<P>
It called upon "the Italian government to take prompt measures
to bring the matter to its proper conclusion without delay."
</P>
<P>
Axum obelisks are most striking relics of ancient Axum Kingdom
established about 2,000 years ago in Axum, an ancient city
located 600 kilometers north of Addis Ababa.
</P>
<P>
They are made of single blocks of granite carved in the
representation of multi-storey buildings. The tallest, now
fallen, stood over 33 meters high and represented a building of
13 storeys. The biggest obelisk still standing is 23 meters high
with about 10 storeys. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970109.0066 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
