<HEADLINE> Lu Ping Meets HK Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Lu Ping, director of the Hong
Kong and Macao Affairs Office of the State Council, said here
today that the first Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) shall be responsible for the formation
of the first SAR government before Hong Kong's return to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Provisional Legislative Council shall prepare
for the legislation for the SAR, although it will not gain the
full extent of its authority until July 1, this year, he added.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with a delegation from the Chinese General Chamber
of Commerce of Hong Kong led by its Chairman Tsang Hin Chi, Lu
said Tung Chee-hwa, the first Chief Executive, must nominate the
principal officials of the future SAR government, report them to
the central people's government for appointment, and also
designate members of the Executive Council in accordance with the
decision adopted at the National People's Congress, before July 1.
</P>
<P>
To do all of this after July 1 will only complicate the
formation of the SAR government, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the entire legislative process of the
Provisional Legislative Council will not be accomplished until the
zero hour of July 1, when the Chief Executive signs a decree.
</P>
<P>
All of its work before July 1 is only to prepare for the
legislation of the SAR, and avoid a legal vacuum, he emphasized.
</P>
<P>
Lu said it is less than half a year before Hong Kong returns to
the motherland, and Hong Kong is currently operating well overall,
thanks to the efforts made over the years by the majority of the
Hong Kong people, including those present.
</P>
<P>
Tsang said the Chinese General Chamber of Commerce of Hong Kong
will continue to carry forward the spirit of loving the motherland
and Hong Kong, go all out to participate in the work concerned
with Hong Kong's return, and contribute to the region's smooth
transition and its prosperity and stability.  
</P>
</TEXT>
