<DOCNO> XIE19970109.0081 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Lauds Taxation Workers for Record Tax Revenue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji
has commended the country's taxation workers for their diligent
efforts to collect record-breaking taxes last year.
</P>
<P>
Latest official statistics show that China's industrial and
commercial tax revenue grew by more than 100 billion yuan to 644.6
billion yuan (about 77.6 billion US dollars) in 1996.
</P>
<P>
It's the first time that the tax revenue expanded by more than
100 billion yuan year-on-year, and the fourth consecutive year
that it grew by more than 96 billion yuan annually.
</P>
<P>
The record industrial and commercial tax revenue, which also
means that China overfulfilled its tax target for six years in a
row, was up 19.7 percent over 1995 and represented 107 percent of
last year's goal.
</P>
<P>
Zhu wrote in a report by the State Administration of Taxation,
"Please pass my heartfelt thanks and gratitude to all the taxation
workers for the great achievements they scored in 1996."
</P>
<P>
A breakdown shows that the domestic value-added tax and
consumption tax, two major tax items under China's new
revenue-sharing taxation regime introduced in 1994, rose 14
percent to 365.7 billion yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
When corporate income taxes and other earnings are included,
China's fiscal income exceeded the mark of 700 billion yuan to
714.7 billion yuan in 1996, up 16.8 percent over a year ago.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970109.0082 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. African Women's Hockey for Olympics Soars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The South African Women's
Hockey Team will be assured of their place in the Sydney Olympics
in 2000 if they maintain their position as Africa's top outfit,
local sport experts said today.
</P>
<P>
The International Olympic Committee have agreed to increase
the number of teams in the women's hockey competition from eight
to 10 teams -- which means that each continent's champion will
automatically qualify, the experts said.
</P>
<P>
South Africa are currently the All Africa Games and Africa Cup
champions and are currently ranked in the top 12 of all 115
hockey playing nations.
</P>
<P>
The team are currently preparing to playing Olympic bronze
medalist Holland in a test series next month to sharpen their
skills for the World Cup qualifier in Harare in August.
</P>
<P>
A top six finish in Harare will ensure qualification for the
1998 World Cup in Utrecht of the Netherlands, the experts said.
</P>
</TEXT>
