<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani caretaker Prime
Minister Malik Miraj Khalid today ordered emergency financial aid
to victims of a chlorine leakage accident in Lahore.
</P>
<P>
Khalid also urged that other emergency steps be taken to help
the victims of the accident, which occurred Wednesday in Lahore,
capital of Punjab Province, killing 20 people and injuring 400
others.
</P>
<P>
He directed immediate payment of 50,000 rupees (about 1,250
U.S. dollars) to compensate the family of each dead.
</P>
<P>
