Khalid offered his sympathy to the bereaved families and assured
them that every possible effort would be made to help them.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister, meanwhile, directed the local authorities
to undertake an immediate evaluation of other losses including the
loss of cattle to finalize a separate compensation package.
</P>
<P>
Caretaker Punjab Chief Minister Mian Afzal Hayat today visited
the victims at a hospital in Lahore where they were receiving
treatment, according to local press reports.
</P>
<P>
He inquired about the health of the victims and assured them of
all possible help from the provincial government.
</P>
<P>
He also directed the hospital management to extend all possible
medical aid to the victims, free of charge.  
</P>
