<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The Customs and Excise
Department of Hong Kong and the Tobacco Institute of Hong Kong
Limited have renewed the agreement of a reward scheme with 500,000
HK dollars for inviting information on illicit cigarettes,
according to Hong Kong Customs.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the Customs said Wednesday that by the end of
November 1996, Hong Kong Customs seized 371 million cigarettes, an
increase of 50 million over the same period of 1995.
