<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia, Thailand Sign MOU on Health Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia and Thailand
signed here today a memorandum of understanding (MOU) to provide
for closer cooperation in the area of health including disease
surveillance along their common border.
</P>
<P>
Under the MOU, the two countries will exchange epidemiological
information and cooperate in training health personnel.
</P>
<P>
They will also engage in joint research and studies which are
essential components of disease control and jointly implement
procedures governing food and drug inspection on the border with a
view to checking the outbreaks of diseases.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia and Thailand will also cooperate in research on
non-communicable diseases such as plague and ebola virus infection
and environmental issues.
</P>
<P>
The MOU also covers diseases such as anthrax, rabies, typhus
and foot and mouth disease which has a potential to affect humans.
</P>
<P>
The MOU was proposed during the 13th Malaysia/Thailand Border
Health Conference in Johore Bahru, Malaysia, in 1992.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
