<HEADLINE> Patent Growing Healthily in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, January 9 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang Province
has handled over a hundred patent disputes in recent years, most
of which have been settled.
</P>
<P>
Now, the number of such disagreements has been curbed,
according to officials in charge of patent issues.
</P>
<P>
The coastal province was one of the first in China to put the
patent affairs on the government agenda, since the Patent Law was
enacted in the country in 1985.
</P>
<P>
Over the past decade, 11 patent administrative agencies and
nearly 30 patent affairs offices have been set up across the
province, receiving more than 20,000 applications for patents and
granting over 10,000 patent rights.
</P>
<P>
The newly-added value brought in by the patented products has
reached seven billion yuan, according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
More applications for patents come from enterprises than
research institutes and schools of higher learning, according to
sources.  
</P>
</TEXT>
