<HEADLINE> Enterprises Encouraged to be More Active in Science Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Enterprises in east China's
Zhejiang Province are encouraged by local authorities to play a
greater role in science research.
</P>
<P>
Special awards have been set up to encourage enterprises as
well as research institutes to advance local economy by using more
sophisticated technology, according to officials.
</P>
<P>
At an annual ceremony to honor major scientific achievements,
the majority of the 300 prize-winning projects were joint efforts
involving enterprises and research institutes. More than 80
percent of the achievements targeted national economic sectors,
and half deal with energy, communications, materials,
petrochemicals, machine building, and light and textile industries.
</P>
<P>
Many of the successes have played an important role in the
renovation and upgrading of enterprises, officials said.
</P>
<P>
In the past three years, 300 achievements have yielded 20
billion yuan-worth of newly-added value, provincial statistics
show.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has asked major enterprises to set up
their research organs and try to upgrade their products on their
own.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, the gross domestic product of the
province has increased at an annual rate of 19.1 percent, and its
major economic index ranking has risen from the seventh to fifth
in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
