<HEADLINE> China Approves Bond Issue for Gigantic Water Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- China will issue one billion
yuan (about 120 million US dollars) in bonds for the gigantic
Three Gorges Project, the China Yangtze Three Gorges Development
Corp., the issuer, announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The bond issue, the first by the corporation inside China, has
been approved by the State Planning Commission and rated AAA- by
the China Chengxin Securities Rating Co. Ltd. The bonds fall into
the category of corporate bonds for enterprises directly run by
the central authorities.
</P>
<P>
"Raising funds through issuing bonds fits perfectly well into a
large project like the Three Gorges Water Project," an expert said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the water conservancy project, the largest in the
world, will take a long time to build and will need extensive
funding at the early stage of construction.
</P>
<P>
However, it will produce a huge return during the later stage
of construction, and power generated by the project will sell
well, the expert said.
</P>
<P>
"Pooling funds directly from the market is an important
guarantee for the smooth construction of the Three Gorges
Project," he said.
</P>
<P>
Approved and authorized by related governments, the issuer will
guarantee the bonds in full value with a special construction fund
for the Three Gorges Project, which is expected to cost 90 billion
yuan in fixed current prices and scheduled to be completed in
about 20 years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
