<HEADLINE> Fewer People But More Goods Being Moved On China's Waterways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- According to a conference on
transportation done over the phone today, China's waterways
carried a total of 220 million passengers last year, a decline of
7.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The country's waterways at the same time carried 1.189 billion
tons of cargo, an increase of 1.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Major seaports in China handled a total of 1.155 billion tons
of cargo last year, a rise of 3.8 percent, and a total of 7.69
million standard containers were handled, a jump of 26.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
There were also improvements to 518 kilometers of waterways,
with total river navigation routes reaching 111,600 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-six new sea port berths were completed last year, adding
3.4 million tons in handling capacity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
