<HEADLINE> China's Foreign Ministry Spokesman On Guatemala Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Ministry spokesman Shen
Guofang said in Beijing today that the Guatemalan government is to
be held fully responsible for all consequences arisen from its
actions which went against the basic principles of the UN Charter.
</P>
<P>
Although it is a good thing to accomplish peace in Guatemala,
he noted, it is regrettable that its government invited the
so-called "Foreign Minister" of the Taiwan authorities to attend
the signing ceremony of the peace agreement, turning a deaf ear to
repeated advices from the Chinese side.
</P>
<P>
Shen's comments came at a press conference in response to
remarks made by Guatemalan Foreign Minister on Monday, who said he
hopes that China will not veto a UN resolution on sending peace
observers to Guatemala.
</P>
<P>
"The Guatemalan government should not expect co-operation from
China at the UN Security Council when it blatantly goes against
the basic principles and aims of the UN Charter and when its
actions are detrimental to China's sovereignty and territorial
integrity," Shen said.
</P>
<P>
China has always supported the peace process in Guatemala and
expresses its welcome to the peace agreement reached by the two
parties, he noted.
</P>
<P>
"The Guatemalan government's actions, which are in violation
of the UN Charter and UN resolution No.2758, have seriously hurt
the national feelings of the Chinese people and undermined the
political basis for co-operation between the two countries at the
United Nations," Shen said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
