<HEADLINE> 9 Soldiers killed, 232 Injured in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Nine government troops were
killed and 232 others wounded in a heavy attack by the Tamil
rebels in Northern Province of Sri Lanka today, according to
Defense Ministry sources here this evening.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that as of 3:00 P.M. today, government troops
from the Elephant Pass area, together with reinforcements, have
linked up with troops from the 54th Division. Consolidation in
this area is in progress.
</P>
<P>
They said nine government troops were killed and 232 others
injured in the action while about 500 rebels were wounded. But the
number of rebel deaths was not known yet.
</P>
<P>
The number of troops killed is likely to increase as a search
is still going on, they pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Early this morning at 04:00, the Tamil rebels launched a heavy
attack on the Task Force Two area at Elephant Pass and Paranthan
army camps.
</P>
<P>
The raid was successfully repulsed by the government troops,
the sources said. 
