<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Ex-President Released from Jail </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi former president
Hosain Mohammed Ershad was released this afternoon after spending
more than 6 years in jail.
</P>
<P>
His release was ordered by the Supreme Court following an
ad-interim bail granted by the court in the radar purchase case
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Pending disposal of the appeal, let the accused-petitioner be
released on ad-interim bail to the satisfaction of the deputy
commissioner (of the Dhaka Central Jail)," ordered the full bench
of the court led by chief justice A.T.M. Afzal.
</P>
<P>
Ershad, 67, chairman of the Jatiya (national) Party (JP), took
power as president of the military regime in 1982 and was put into
jail for corruption and criminal charges just after his forced
step-down in 1990. He faced a number of charges and was accused in
a total 19 cases.
</P>
<P>
So far, the ex-president has been granted bails in 17 cases. He
was acquitted in one case and left out of another in a final
report by investigators.  
</P>
</TEXT>
