<HEADLINE> Taiwan Bank Opens Branch in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 9 (Xinhua) -- A Taiwan bank, the Taipei Business
Bank, inaugurated a branch here today, designed to do business
both in Macao and the neighboring South China region.
</P>
<P>
Ranking the 16th in terms of total deposits among Taiwan banks,
the Taipei Business Bank deals with a wide range of banking
business including money deposit and loans, import and export
business, remittance and bank accounts transfer.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the bank makes investment in various fields.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1948, it is the first Taiwan-based bank doing
business in Macao. Currently, the bank has about 80 branches in
Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
"One of our main objectives is to promote business relations
between Taiwan and Macao, and also between Taiwan and Guangdong
province in the mainland," a spokesman for the bank said.
</P>
<P>
Macao now has 24 banks, including those from the Chinese
mainland, Portugal, the United States, France, Germany and Hong
Kong.  
</P>
