<HEADLINE> China Redoubles Environmental Education Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Environmental protection will be
a course available at China's schools of higher learning soon.
</P>
<P>
Environmental education needs to be increased at schools at all
levels, according to a recent document from the State Bureau of
Environmental Protection, the Propaganda Department of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China, and the State Education
Commission.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the document is to increase public awareness of
environmental protection in China. Schools are being asked to
introduce their students to environmental issues through such
activities as summer and winter camps and composition contests.
</P>
<P>
Training classes will also be started for elementary and middle
school teachers.  
