<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysian PM Unhappy Over Punk Culture Among Youth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad today expressed his unhappiness over the spread
of punk culture by the West among the Malaysian youth.
</P>
<P>
Addressing students of the Malaysia North University in Sintok
near Alor Star, some 460 kilometers north of here, he said he was
amazed how this negative culture could be taken up by these youths
who at the same time ignored many virtues in life.
</P>
<P>
He was quoted by the Malaysian national news agency Bernama as
asking what was the use of the punk culture which he said
advocates violence and unhealthy behavior and "where is the beauty
in nice hair being glued together."
</P>
<P>
Mahathir advised people specially students to have a high level
of self-discipline in their daily life and in pursuing knowledge
and carrying out their duties.
</P>
<P>
Only with a high level of discipline could a person achieve
success in his various endeavors, he said.
</P>
<P>
Students should ponder over their main aim of entering
university and not look upon campus life as a period to just enjoy
themselves.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister also wanted students and other people in the
country to enhance their management skills which are important for
the country to realize its vision of becoming a developed nation
by the year 2020.
</P>
<P>
He said Malaysia's successes could be attributed to efficient
management and this has placed Malaysia among the most successful
developing countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
