<HEADLINE> New Industrial Strategy For Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 9 (Xinhua) -- China's leading industrial
center is developing a modern industrial system by improving its
traditional industries and developing new pillar industries.
</P>
<P>
These include micro-electronics and computers, biological and
pharmaceutical products, new materials, environmental protection,
ship-making, and building materials.
</P>
<P>
Annual output value of new materials is expected to reach 20
billion yuan by the end of the century; and that of the
environment protection industry 12 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
the city will also develop equipment for large thermal and
nuclear power plants and hydroelectric power stations, elevators,
engineering equipment, digitally-controlled machine tools, organic
chemical raw materials, chemical products, motor vehicles, ships,
special steel products, and domestic durables.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Shanghai is concentrating on adjusting its product
mix and technical transformation for brand-name goods.
</P>
<P>
The city's light industry is expected to turn out 12,000 new
products this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
