<HEADLINE> Nigeria Develops Solar-Powered Cellular </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria has developed solar-powered
cellular telephones that can be used as public pay-phones at places
where lines and power supply are not available.
</P>
<P>
According to the local newspaper "Nigerian Tribune" today, the
phone, developed by researchers at the Nigerian
Telecommunications, has a battery that is charged during the day
by solar panels and uses the cellular channels of the public
switch board.
</P>
<P>
It also has an automatic day/night switch which provides
illumination during the night. 
