<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Announces Highway Construction Blueprint </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Completion of 20,000 kilometers
of highways is one of China's major construction projects as
contained in a blueprint announced by the Minister of
Communications Huang Jiandong.
</P>
<P>
The minister said on a telephone conference today that China's
communication sector will use most foreign investment this year
for infrastructure projects and high and new technology.
</P>
<P>
"The BOT (build, operate and transfer) method and issuing of
stocks and bonds will continue to be encouraged in using overseas
funding," the minister explained, noting that "Efforts will also
be made to improve the quality of overseas-financed projects."
</P>
<P>
Of the 20,000 kilometers of highways to be built, 900 are
expressways, and 1,000 are level-one and -two roads.
</P>
<P>
China will also build 28 new deep-water berths, adding 50
million tons to port handling capacity.
</P>
<P>
To improve river transportation, 360 kilometers of navigation
channels on the nation's rivers will be improved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
