<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Decoration Attractive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The decoration industry in
Shanghai, China's largest economic center, is displaying its role
with the improvement of people's living standards.
</P>
<P>
The latest sample survey shows that families moving into new
houses spend an average of 30,000 yuan per family decorating their
homes.
</P>
<P>
Experts in Shanghai predicted that China's decoration industry
will grow at a speed of ten percent annually.
</P>
<P>
By the end of this century, the country is expected to consume
more than 500 million tons of cement, 150 million square meters of
glass products, and 40 million sets of ceramic toilet fittings.
</P>
<P>
The 13 million residents of Shanghai currently have a living
space of eight square meters per head.
</P>
<P>
A municipal official in charge of housing said that the city is
building more residential quarters to ensure its residents have a
living space up to ten sq m per capita by year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Under the plan, some 100,000 households will move into new
dwellings each year, turning home decoration into an even bigger
consumer segment in the coming years.  
</P>
