<DOCNO> XIE19970109.0157 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Airport Has Most Passengers, Cargo in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The Capital International
Airport in Beijing has ranked first place in the number of
passengers and amount of cargo handled.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the passengers and cargo passing through the
airport, the largest and most advanced in the country, have
increased by more than 20 percent yearly.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that 17 million passengers traveled through the
airport in 1996, and 133,000 flights were recorded, carrying
400,000 tons of postal shipments.
</P>
<P>
The airport was accepted as a member of the International
Airport Association last November, becoming the first in China to
join the group.
</P>
<P>
To date, it has opened 69 international air routes linking
Beijing with 56 major cities in 36 countries and regions, and 61
domestic routes reaching all parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
China's airlines carried 56.5 million passengers in 1996, up 10
percent over the previous year, and handled 1.15 million tons of
cargo and postal shipments.  
</P>
</TEXT>
