<BODY>
<HEADLINE> All-round Economic Growth In Northern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 9 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei
Province has met all its economic goals for 1996, with a GDP that
increased by 13 percent, according to the Provincial Statistics
Bureau.
</P>
<P>
An official of the bureau said that as a leading grain
production center in north China, Hebei harvested 27.7 billion kg
of grain, an all time high.
</P>
<P>
Its industry recorded rapid growth, with its added value
increasing 16 percent in 1996, two percentage points higher than
the target.
</P>
<P>
Total investment in fixed assets was 115 billion yuan
last year, 22.4 percent up from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Construction of 129 key projects went well, with a number of
thermal power plants, program-controlled switch boards, and
building materials projects having been completed.
</P>
<P>
Price increases for the first time were lower than the economic
growth rate of 6.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The province held trade fairs in Hong Kong and Xiamen, and the
amount of foreign funds it used in 1996 surged 14 percent to
nearly 1.6 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The annual income of both urban and rural residents increased
substantially and more than one million poor people in rural areas
got out of poverty.  
</P>
</TEXT>
