<HEADLINE> Schools For Poverty-stricken Counties In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- By the end of 1996, every
poverty-stricken county in China's outlying and mountainous areas
had at least one school, thanks to a charity.
</P>
<P>
According to the China Youth Development Fund (CYDF), all 592 of the
poorest counties in China recognized by the central government
have built "Hope Schools", with money donated by people all across
the country.
</P>
<P>
Since "Project Hope" was launched in 1989, money has been
raised by private and institutional donations to help the poor
students return to school.
</P>
<P>
CYDF's Beijing headquarters invested more than 22 million yuan
(2.5 million US dollars) last year in building schools, and its
many branches in different provinces have done all they could to
help.
</P>
<P>
However, there are still 16 million square meters of
dilapidated classrooms that are in need of repair, and the money
shortage problem has still not been solved, a spokesman said.
</P>
