<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Horticultural Earnings Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's horticultural
earnings are expected to reach 150 million U.S. Dollars in 1997,
up from last year's 100 million U.S. Dollars, economists said
here today.
</P>
<P>
The forecasted growth of the horticultural industry will be
fueled mainly by new export markets being explored by local
producers, they said.
</P>
<P>
Auctions in the Netherlands have been the biggest outlet for
Zimbabwean horticultural products. But the market demand is
changing rapidly in Europe with falling prices and environmental
concerns forcing producers.
</P>
<P>
So far some have successfully diversified exports from the
Dutch auction system to new markets in Japan, Taiwan, Dubai,
Mauritius, Singapore and Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, citrus exports this year are anticipated to be much
higher than the 30,000 ton record last year, mainly due to the
introduction of new high-yield varieties of better quality in
terms of colour, taste and shape. 
</P>
