<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Buhe, vice chairman of the
Standing Committee of China's National People's Congress (NPC),
said in Beijing today that parliamentary exchanges between China
and Sweden will help promote friendship and cooperative ties.
</P>
<P>
He made the statement during a meeting with a Swedish
parliament delegation composed of members of the country's largest
party, the ruling Social Democratic Party.
</P>
<P>
Buhe said Sweden was the first western country to establish
diplomatic relations with the People's Republic of China. For over
40 years, since the two countries forged official ties, bilateral
relations have greatly advanced, with increasing exchanges between
the two parliaments. He said he hopes such exchanges would further
the bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Marianne Carlstroem, head of the delegation, said Sweden is
presently faced with problems similar to China, citing particular
concerns over economic growth and a population problem. She added
that she believes the current visit to China will help deepen
understanding of the country.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting the NPC vice chairman also briefed the
guests on China's economic development, and the NPC's efforts in
setting up the legal framework for a socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish delegation arrived in Beijing on January 4 at the
invitation of NPC for a 12-day friendly visit.  
