<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hi-Tech Development Boosts Shanghai's Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Hi-tech industries in Shanghai
developed rapidly in 1996, with total output topping 50 billion
yuan, a 6.4 billion yuan increase over the previous year,
according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the hi-tech sector made up 12 percent of the city's
entire industrial output, which is estimated to have surpassed 400
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has 496 hi-tech enterprises which belong to the city's
six pillar industries, including automobiles, telecommunications
and power generation equipment sectors. Seventy-two percent of
the hi-tech firms are run solely with domestic capital.
</P>
<P>
Among the hi-tech companies, Sino-foreign joint ventures and
solely-foreign-funded firms experienced a fast development in
1996, with their total production making up 42 per cent of the
sector.
</P>
<P>
In 1996 most of the local hi-tech firms achieved record
economic returns, with per-capita output value topping 200,000
yuan, 20,000 yuan more than the figure in the previous year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
