<HEADLINE> Petrol Prices Drop in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Shell Uganda, the leading oil
products dealer in the country, cut petrol and kerosene prices on
Wednesday, the local newspaper "The People" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The petrol price fell by 11 cents to about one U.S. Dollar per
liter, the first time that petrol prices have been cut since last
August in Uganda.
</P>
<P>
The petrol prices rose in the country in August last
year and went up successively in October and November.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the price cut is that Uganda's local currency
Shilling has since last November appreciated against the U.S.
Dollar, ending a steady trend of depreciation since July last
year. 
</P>
