<HEADLINE> Chang Moves into Colonial Classic Tennis Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 9 (Xinhua) -- American Michael Chang
overwhelmed Boris Becker of Germany in a three-set marathon
semi-final at the Colonial Classic tennis tournament in Melbounre
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Chang saved three match points on his way to a 2-6, 6-4, 7-6
(7-5) win which took him two hours 18 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Becker served for 5-4 in the final set but the world No. 2
American staved off the match points to force a tiebreaker.
</P>
<P>
Chang, trailing 0-4 in the tiebreaker, came back strongly to
win the match.
</P>
<P>
The eight-man Colonial Classic is the final warm-up tournament
before the Australian Open starts on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Chang will play the winner of Friday's semi-final between world
No. 1 Pete Sampras of the United States and French Open champion
Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia in Saturday's final.
</P>
<P>
Thomas Enqvist of Sweden, seeded seventh in the Australian
Open, pulled out of his consolation match against Andrei Medvedev
of Ukraine because of a blister on his right hand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
