<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Unemployment Rate Under One Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Unemployment in China's capital
been kept at under one percent for the 11th successive
year. Economists say that Beijing has done a marvelous job in
keeping down its jobless rate.
</P>
<P>
The level is counted in fractions, even though 100,000 job-
hunters swell the ranks of the city's labor force each year.
</P>
<P>
Beijing now has more than 200 employment agencies, 100
occupation training centers and dozens of labor dispute
arbitration institutes.
</P>
<P>
The occupation introduction, employment training, unemployment
insurance and labor service companies, have been the four pillars
serving the local labor market, creating an orderly system.
</P>
<P>
A new unemployment insurance system guarantees 189 yuan (about
22.7 US dollars) in relief per month for each laid-off worker in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Sources claim that the number of people in the local labor
market is greater than the number of jobs available. And there
were 205,300 people who registered for jobs at employment agencies
in the third quarter of 1996, with only 149,000 openings available
in 6,830 companies and institutions.
</P>
<P>
Governments at all levels are doing their utmost to ensure jobs
for laid-offs, and to help jobless people maintain their minimum
living standard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
