<DOCNO> XIE19970109.0208 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Opens Business in Shares for Foreign Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- China Securities Regulatory
Commission will soon start to handle applications for business in
shares for overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
"It is time to get required material ready if securities
businesses, either domestic or foreign, wish to receive an
admission approval," said a spokesman for the commission.
</P>
<P>
According to a set of rules issued in mid-December, securities
institutions, both inside and outside China, will need to acquire
an official permit in order to remain in the securities business
to deal in shares for overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
To qualify for the brokerage business of such shares, overseas
securities companies need to have a minimum asset value of 50
million yuan, an official guarantee by their own government, at
least two years of experience in foreign securities business,
efficient management personnel, and a good record in abiding by
the law, said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Application forms are available for domestic securities
companies in local offices of the commission, while overseas
companies need to acquire them directly from the commission's head
office in Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
