<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Refugees Rush Into Tanzania From Zaire, Burundi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Refugees from Zaire and
Burundi continue to flock across the border into Tanzania since
the beginning of 1997.
</P>
<P>
About 4,260 refugees fleeing the fresh fighting in Zaire have
arrived in Kigomba, Northern Tanzania, and the influx shows no
signs of abating, according to the United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) today.
</P>
<P>
So far 2,911 Zaireans have fled mainly from the towns of
Uvira, Yungu, Fizi and Malindi in eastern Zaire, arriving by
UNHCR boats to Kibirizi Port although some found their own way
through Lake Tanganyika by illegal means.
</P>
<P>
And 1,349 Burundian refugees, reported to be in a
significantly poorer state of health, arrived mostly on foot.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
