<HEADLINE> Nearly One Million Headmasters Trained </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- About 90 percent of China's
school headmasters received special training last year in a move
to improve their school management capabilities, "China Education
Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
Only those who obtained special certificates of completion can
remain in their posts, according to the paper.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted a UNESCO official as praising the idea, and
that a record one million headmasters were targeted in the
national program.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, most of them attended long or short term classes
opened by the State Education Committee and provincial education
centers.
</P>
<P>
Education is the first priority in the economic and social
development program of modern China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
