<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Halts Fish Export to Middle East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Fishery and
Marketing Enterprise said on Wednesday that it has temporarily
halted fish export to the Middle East countries due to the
increase in domestic demand.
</P>
<P>
Solomon Tafesse, administrative manager of the enterprise,
said the seven-year export suspension began since last October.
</P>
<P>
He added that the export would resume with the local market
satisfied and surplus production attained.
</P>
<P>
The enterprise used to obtain 75,000 U.S. Dollars annually
from the 15-ton export of fish.
</P>
<P>
The annual sale of fish by the enterprise stands at 1,400
tons on average to the local market. 
</P>
