<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Beijing is to introduce more
investments from abroad to promote energy-saving, pollution-free,
and technology-intensive industries in the coming years.
</P>
<P>
An official at the municipal government said that Beijing will
give top priority to such industries as electronic information,
automobiles, numeric machine tools, machinery equipment, new
materials, high-grade garments and chemicals.
</P>
<P>
Foreign companies are also being encouraged to invest in these
industries, the official said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Chinese capital will lure more overseas
investment to transform its existing manufacturers.
</P>
