Beijing has industrial fixed assets valued at 100 billion yuan,
and an annual gross industrial output of 120 billion yuan, ranking
second in the country after Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Transnational companies as Pepsi Co. Inc. of the United States,
Siemens of Germany, Philips of the Netherlands and Matsushita
Electric Company of Japan, have launched business operations in
the city, which has more than 8,000 foreign-funded companies.
</P>
<P>
