<HEADLINE> Telecom Development in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province
will step up development in the post and telecommunications sector
this year, with annual business volume expected to exceed 10
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
According to the provincial development plan, which appeared in
the latest issue of "People's Posts and Telecommunications," the
number of telephone users will rise by one million, and about two
million telephone lines will be added to the province's telecom
system.
</P>
<P>
The plan calls for posts and telecommunications volume to reach
11.9 billion yuan this year.
</P>
<P>
The number of subscribers for local telephone networks will
increase by 1.15 million, and there will be 300,000 cellular phone
users.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997, the telephone density rate will be 12
percent, and a province-level intelligent network and four
city-level narrow-band ISDN (integrated service digital network)
systems will come into operation.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu now has 4.5 million phone customers and 220,000 for
mobile telephones, with a telephone density rate of 10 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
