<HEADLINE> Fujian Expands Mobile Telephone Systems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province has
clinched a deal with Motorola, the leading mobile telephone
supplier in the U.S., to expand its mobile phone systems.
</P>
<P>
According to "People's Posts and Telecommunications News," the
contract involving 108 million US dollars stipulates that the
province will use the Motorola products to upgrade both its
digital and analog cellular phone networks.
</P>
<P>
When completed, the GSM (global service for mobile
communication) and TACS services will extend their coverage to the
whole province, with the combined switching capacity increased
from 280,000 handsets to 490,000.
</P>
<P>
Beside the mobile phone networks, the province's posts and
telecom bureau will allow Motorola to establish a pilot DCS1800
system there, the paper said. 
</P>
