<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Campaign to Promote Consumer Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Consumers'
Association and local consumers groups will progress their efforts
to safeguard consumers rights in 1997 by continuing a campaign for
honest and sincere services and cracking down on illegal
activities, China Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
"We will fix a theme for our work every year to better
publicize the legal rights of consumers and to promote development
of consumer care in China," Cao Tiandian, director of the national
consumer association, is quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese consumers' association (CCA) has 2,809 county-level
consumer groups around the country.
</P>
<P>
"The reason for fixing this year's theme is that the practice
of making and marketing fake and inferior goods and the activities
of cheating consumers are still serious. Effective measures are
needed to cope with the problem," Cao said.
</P>
<P>
The theme is not just a "propaganda slogan", he said, and
should inform all the efforts by consumer organizations to protect
the rights of consumers this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
