<HEADLINE> Lubricant Oil Sales Predicted Up 14.2 Pc in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Sales of lubricant oil in
Thailand are expected to reach 400 million litters this year, up
14.2 percent from 1996, the Thai Farmers Research Center predicts.
</P>
<P>
The center says that 44 percent of the total sales of lubricant
oil in the country is likely to be for cars, 10 percent for
motorcycles, and 8.5 percent for factory machinery.
</P>
<P>
The reminder will be sold for aircraft, cargo ships, and
construction and farm machinery.
</P>
<P>
Foreign lubricant oil dealers currently dominate Thailand's
lubricant oil market. Shell accounts for 29 percent of the total
lubricant oil sales in Thailand, while Esso claims 27 percent,
Caltex 18 percent and Mobil 11 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Petroleum Authority of Thailand only has a 9 percent share
of the market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
