<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Army Repulses Rebels Attack In North </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
repulsed a major attack of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam
(LTTE) rebels in the Northern province of the country today,
according to military sources here.
</P>
<P>
The sources told Xinhua in telephone that a fierce LTTE attack
on the army camp at Elephant Pass in the south of the Jaffna
Peninsula this morning has been repulsed by the government troops.
</P>
<P>
The attack commenced around 05:00 this morning and was
effectively repulsed with the rebels forced to flee after
suffering heavy casualties after three hours of fighting, the
sources added.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a guerrilla war for a separate state
in the north and east of the country since 1983.  
</P>
