<HEADLINE> Bangladesh, Britain to Sign Pact on Gas Exploration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh and Britain will sign
an agreement on gas exploration during the three-day official
visit of British Prime Minister John Major to Dhaka from Friday
evening.
</P>
<P>
According to reliable sources, the agreement will be initiated
by Petrobangla, the state-run petro corporation in Bangladesh, and
a British company.
</P>
<P>
It was learnt that Major will arrive in Dhaka Friday evening
from India's Calcutta.
</P>
<P>
The visit to Dhaka will be the second leg of Major's
three-nation tour of the subcontinent, which will also take him to
Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Major will have official talks with his Bangladesh counterpart
Sheikh Hasina, covering the entire gamut of bilateral relations as
well as regional and international issues of common concern, the
sources said, adding that the official talks will take up matters
relating to the expansion of trade and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Britain, the second largest importer of Bangladeshi products,
imported goods worth about 450 million U.S. dollars from
Bangladesh in 1995-1996. Balance of trade is in favor of
Bangladesh as Britain exported commodities including machinery and
chemicals valued at 130 million dollars to Bangladesh during the
same period.
</P>
<P>
The whole range of the visit is seen as an important attempt to
revitalize the kingdom's political, economic and trade relations
with its former colony, a concerned official here said. 
</P>
