<HEADLINE> 20 Killed, 400 Injured in Chlorine Leak in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Twenty people were killed and
more than 400 others fell unconscious Wednesday night in a
chlorine gas leakage in Lahore, capital city of Punjab province.
</P>
<P>
Local press reported here today, the poisonous vapors of lethal
chlorine gas leaked from cylinders loaded on a truck which got
stuck in a pit.
</P>
<P>
As the driver tried to pull the vehicle out, moving it back and
forth rapidly, the drums placed in the truck fell down, resulting
in the chlorine leak.
</P>
<P>
The truck was carrying two cylinders of liquefied chlorine to a
chemical plant.
</P>
<P>
Police reached the scene after an hour. Army, heavy contingents
of police, doctors and ambulances were called in.
</P>
<P>
People who fell unconscious were rushed to nearby hospitals.
</P>
