<HEADLINE> Mongolian Population Reaches 2.35 Million 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The population of Mongolia
reached 2.35 million by the end of 1996, 35,800 more than that of
the previous year, according to the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia encourages child birth due to its vast areas, with its
population increasing from 772,400 to 2.15 million between
1950-1990, the peak period of population growth in the nation's
history.
</P>
<P>
However, the growth rate slowed down in recent years because of
the change in people's view on population and their living
standard. 
</P>
