<HEADLINE> Crime Rate Increases in Mongolia in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, January 9 (Xinhua) -- A total of 22,368 criminal
cases were recorded in Mongolia in 1996, a 9.1-percent increase
over last year, local newspapers reported today.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the crimes resulted in 987 deaths, 4,344
injuries and an economic loss of 11.5 billion Tugriks (about 166
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Of the crimes, that caused by alcoholism remained very serious
with 87,736 alcoholists forced into hospital last year, a
10-percent increase over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The figures also show that of the total criminal cases, 9,917
were committed in the capital Ulan Bator. The other cities whose
cases exceeded 1,000 are Khentei Aimak, Selenge and Darkhan.
</P>
