<HEADLINE> Belarusian GDP Up in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The gross domestic product (GDP)
of Belarus rose 2 percent in 1996 over the previous year,
reversing the downward trend in the past five consecutive years.
</P>
<P>
However, the sales issue was not solved as the nation still
overstocked goods valued 10 trillion roubles (about 400 million
U.S. dollars) at the end of 1996, which accounted for 6 percent of
last year's GDP total, according to the Interfax news agency today.
</P>
<P>
Belarus will speed up the privatization of commerce and
tertiary industry in 1997 in a bid to bail out the debt-laden
state-run enterprises, Interfax quoted a ranking government
official as saying.
</P>
<P>
This year, the country will also promulgate a bankruptcy
law. But the law will not cover large state-run industrial
enterprises at the initial stage.
</P>
<P>
Instead, the large enterprises could extricate themselves from
economic predicament through the establishment of financial and
industrial groups and trans-national corporations, the officials
said. 
</P>
