<HEADLINE> Clinton: U.S. Continues to Maintain Force to Deter Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 8 (Xinhua) -- President Bill Clinton said
on Wednesday that the United States will maintain its effort to
see sanctions remain in force against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
In a report to the Congress, covering the period from November
4 up to the present, Clinton said: "Iraq remains a serious threat
to regional peace and stability. I remain determined to see Iraq
comply fully with all of its obligations under U.N. Security
Council resolutions."
</P>
<P>
