<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Audio-Video Chain Stores to Be Built in Post Offices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- China's first State-owned
audio-video leasing chain store company was established yesterday
in Beijing, reported today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
With approval from the Ministry of Culture, Zhong You
Audio-Video Leasing Co Ltd was built by the China Audio-Video
Association (CAVA) and the China Post under the Ministry of Posts
and Telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
The company will operate chain store rental shops of audio and
video tapes inside urban and rural postal offices nationwide.
Tapes will include Chinese and foreign movies, TV dramas, popular
science and education as well as agricultural technology.
</P>
<P>
During a ceremony at the Great Hall of the People yesterday,
a government official said it was a wise decision by the
government to curb intellectual property rights (IPR) violations
and combat pornography and other illegal publications.
</P>
<P>
CAVA estimates that at present, there are more than 100,000
audio-video rental locations nationwide, nearly all of which are
privately-operated. Many of them rent pirated and pornographic
tapes.
</P>
<P>
Sources with Zhong You said that they plan to establish 2,000
rental shops in 1997, and gradually set up shops in nearly 61,900
post offices across the country.
</P>
<P>
They said that each rental shop will carry 600 kinds of
audio-video tapes.
</P>
<P>
Annual rental business is estimated to reach at least 230
million yuan (27.7 million US dollars), they said, basing the
estimate on the fact that the rental of each tape will cost two
yuan (24 cents).
</P>
<P>
More than 500 post offices in Liaoning Province and in cities
of Hangzhou, Fuzhou and Nanjing have become the first since last
month to install rental shops on a trial basis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
