Romanian products, the Foreign Ministry said today.
</P>
<P>
Spokeswomen Gilda Lazar said a Romanian delegation will go to
Iraq in February to discuss details of oil imports, while Romanian
companies will, through the country's embassy in Baghdad, discuss
the export of food, medicine and other humanitarian materials to
Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi economy has been devastated by an international
sanction since the 1991 Gulf War.
</P>
<P>
In order to alleviate the suffering of ordinary people, the
U.N. Security Council passed a resolution in April last year to
allow Iraq to sell 2 billion U.S. dollars worth of oil half a year
so that it can buy products for everyday use.
</P>
<P>
The resolution went into effect last December. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
