<HEADLINE> Brazilian President Signs Water Bill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian President Fernando
Henrique Cardoso today signed a bill outlining the national policy
on water resources.
</P>
<P>
Environment Minister Gustavo Krause said that under the new
bill, Brazil would assume the commitments of the Agenda 21 signed
during the 1992 Rio Summit.
</P>
<P>
The bill accepts the new concept of sustainable development and
treats water as a strategic natural resource.
</P>
<P>
Krause said the bill would help the nation better understand
the importance of water and appreciate the environmental impact
when using the resource to meet social development needs. 
</P>
