<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Albania's Tourism Develops Rapidly in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The year 1996 witnessed a rapid
development in Albania's tourism.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, the number of foreign tourists who
visited Albania last year quadrupled that of 1995. Foreign
tourists who spent at least one night in the country exceeded
100,000 while the number of domestic tourists increased to
300,000, more than double that of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
With a long coastline, non-polluted sea and pleasant weather,
Albania has favorable natural conditions for developing tourism.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian government has adopted many preferential policies
to encourage investment in tourism.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, investment from Albania's private and foreign
businesses in tourism rose to 60 million U.S. dollars, while
hotels increased to 120 from the previous year's 44.
</P>
<P>
In the southwestern coast area off the Ionian Sea, family
tourism has emerged. Motels and tourist villages are attracting
hundreds and thousands of visitors from Italy and Greece. 
</P>
</TEXT>
