<HEADLINE> China Calls for Correct Use of Chinese Language </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The State Language Work
Committee has decided to launch a new campaign this year to
encourage the correct use of the Chinese language.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the committee in Beijing said that an
investigation will be conducted nationwide to find out whether
railway and airline workers are qualified in the use of their
mother tongue. And the use of Putonghua, or standard Chinese, will
be encouraged to replace the use of local dialects in major public
offices, sources said.
</P>
<P>
The committee will also make efforts to standardize the usage
of Chinese characters in computer language.
</P>
<P>
It will also train more workers to help promote the Chinese
language, and do related research, sources said. 
</P>
