<HEADLINE> Jordan Tops East Players in All-Star Voting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, Janaury 8 (Xinhua) -- Basketball superstar Michael
Jordan is leading the vote-getter of Eastern Conference fan
balloting for the 1997 NBA All-Star Game to be held on Febuary 9.
</P>
<P>
The Chicago Bulls guard, a 10-time All-Star, has 403,665 votes
to overtake forward Grant Hill of the Detroit Pistons, who led all
players in votes received the last two seasons.
</P>
