<HEADLINE> Dutch Foreign Minister Winds Up Visit to Sweden </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, January 8 (Xinhua)-- Dutch Foreign Minister Hans van
Mierlo today wound up the two-day visit to Sweden, the first leg
of his tour of the European Union member states.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands holds the EU chairmanship for the first six
months of this year.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, the Dutch foreign minister held talks with
his Swedish counterpart Lena Hjelm-Wallen and Prime Minister
Goeran Persson. They discussed the EU inter-government conference
