<HEADLINE> Brazil to Provide Aid to Flood-stricken States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian President Fernando
Henrique Cardoso today announced an immediate disbursement of 15
million U.S. dollars for the flood-stricken eastern states of
Minas Gerais, Rio de Janeiro and Espiritu Santo.
</P>
<P>
Cardoso said the money will be used to repair the federal
highways in the three states hardest hit by floods due to heavy
rains.
</P>
<P>
The president emphasized that the situation in these states is
a great concern to the whole country. Some 65,000 people have
been left homeless.
</P>
<P>
In the state of Minas Gerais, floods have claimed 76 lives in
the past week and caused property damage to 42,800 people in 179
municipalities.
</P>
<P>
In Rio de Janeiro, floods hit 15 municipalities, leaving 16,410
people homeless.
</P>
<P>
The city of Cardoso Moreira is the worst-hit place, where over
95 percent of the 11,000 inhabitants have been driven out of their
homes by the overflows of the nearby Muriae River.
</P>
<P>
In Espiritu Santo, floods have affected the normal life of
6,160 people in nine municipalities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
