<HEADLINE> Iranian Foreign Minister Ends Visit to Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Ali Akbar
Velayati left here today for home after concluding a two-day
official visit to Italy.
</P>
<P>
Iranian sources described the visit as a "new chapter in
bilateral ties," while Italian diplomatic sources said it had been
a "useful and satisfying" encounter on the spirit of the European
Union's "critical dialogue" with Tehran.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Velayati held talks with his Italian
counterpart Lamberto Dini on bilateral ties and the relations
between Iran and the EU.
</P>
<P>
Dini stressed that Italian firms have great interest in Iran
and that his government is willing to boost trade with the Gulf
nation, which is Italy's major energy supplier.
</P>
<P>
Velayati also met with Prime Minister Romani Prodi, Senate
President Nicola Mancino and President of Chamber of Deputies
Luciano Violante. 
</P>
</TEXT>
