<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Villeurbanne Edges Pau-Orthez in EuroLeague </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, Janauray 8 (Xinhua) - American Delaney Rudd scored 27
points as Villeurbanne shocked Pau-Orthez 97-95 in an all-French
opener to the second phase of the men's basketball EuroLeague on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Rudd, helped by Brian Howard's 16 and Alain Digbeu's 14, hit a
three-point shot with one minute left as Villeurbanne equalled the
score 95-95.
</P>
<P>
Pau's star skipper Antoine Rigaudeau, back in action after an
elbow injury, missed an easy chance on the counter-attack,
allowing Rudd to make a decisive pass to Jim Bilba, who smashed in
the winner with final five seconds to play in the game of the
Group G.
</P>
<P>
Lawrence Funderdburke led Pau-Orthez with 21 points, His
teammates Frederic Fauthoux and Thierry Gadou added 14 each.
</P>
<P>
In other game of Group G, Spanish Sevilla scored a 81-76
victory over Slovenian Ljubljana.
</P>
<P>
In Group H in Leverkusen, Turkey's Efes Pilsen beat Germany's
Bayer Leverkusen 73-72. 
</P>
</TEXT>
