<HEADLINE> Ukraine Overhauls Tanks for Uzbekistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine has finished overhauling
and upgrading 40 tanks for Uzbekistan, according to the Ukrainian
Defense Ministry today.
</P>
<P>
The overhaul was carried out under a contract between the two
former Soviet republics, which brought Ukraine more than 3.2
million U.S. dollars. Uzbekistan paid 80,200 dollars for each
T-72m.
</P>
<P>
The Kiev Tank Repairing Factory has installed some special
parts in the tanks to enhance their performance.
</P>
<P>
After the overhaul, the 40 T-72m tank will get an extra life
span of more than 3,000 kilometers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
