<HEADLINE> Higuita Back to Training </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Flamboyant Colombian goalkeeper
Rene Higuita took part in a training session on Wednesday with his
former club Atletico Nacional, but it was not clear whether he
would come out of retirement.
</P>
<P>
The 30-year-old Higuita turned up at the club in Medellin, just
over two weeks after his home was bombed by unidentified attackers.
</P>
<P>
Coach Juan Jose Pelez refused to confirm that Higuita, who quit
in November for "personal reasons", was making a comeback.
</P>
<P>
"He wants to return but he has his own struggle," said the
coach. 
</P>
