<HEADLINE> World Top Squash Player Banned for One Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 8 (Xinhua) -- World No. 1 Jansher Khan has been
fined 1,000 pounds (1,690 dollars) and suspended for one month by
the Professional Squash Association (PSA) for his withdrawal from
last month's Mahindra International Challenge in Bombay, India.
</P>
<P>
It was Jansher's fourth withdrawal from a PSA event in a year.
</P>
<P>
Jansher cited "threats to his saftey" as the reason for failing
to compete in the Bombay event, the second richest on the 1996 PSA
World Tour.
</P>
<P>
The PSA said they couldn't find any evidence to prove Jansher's
claim. 
</P>
