<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IRA Message Links Peace to Unification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The Irish Republican Army (IRA)
today issued a tough new year message, insisting that it is
committed to peace in Northern Ireland.
</P>
<P>
"We approach the year ahead unified, confident and steadfast in
our commitment to succeed," said IRA commanders declaring that
their primary objective was a reunited Ireland free of British
influence.
</P>
<P>
The message issued in Dublin commended those who were aiming at
"inclusive negotiations with the goal of attaining a lasting peace
settlement."
</P>
<P>
"No amount of British obduracy will deflect us from the task we
have set ourselves," said the message, issued just days before the
resumption of all-party talks in Belfast from which Sinn Fein is
excluded.
</P>
<P>
According to the message, the IRA guerrillas want a voice in
the talks and will keep on fighting until Britain lets them take
part. 
</P>
</TEXT>
