<HEADLINE> European Shares All Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Leading stock markets in Europe
all surged and ended higher today, boosted by Wall Street's
overnight gains, strengthening dollar and firm bond market.
</P>
<P>
British shares in London struggled to make headway as a
faltering Dow dragged the FTSE 100 leading shares down from early
highs.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, calls by the Bank of England deputy governor for a
0.25 percent interest rate rise kept many players away as
attention focused on specific areas, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE 100 index closed up 8.7 at 4,087.5.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, share prices closed higher in moderate trading,
buoyed by overnight gains on Wall Street and a firmer bond market,
with the DAX-30 index 20.21 up at 2,906.34, just short of its
record closing high.
</P>
<P>
The Paris bourse also ended comfortably higher, backed by the
Dow's new record close and the dollar's strength, with the CAC-40
index up 29.93 at 2,331.62.
</P>
<P>
London's FTSE 100 leading British shares ended 8.7 higher at
4,087.5. The Frankfurt DAX-30 index finished up 20.21 at 2,906,34.
In Paris, the CAC-40 index closed 29.93 up at 2,331.62.
</P>
</TEXT>
