<DOCNO> XIE19970109.0304 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Election Results in Nis to Be Recognized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The Serbian government expects
the election commission in Nis to repeal its decision on repeating
the vote in 17 precincts and recognize the results of the
elections, said a statement issued by the Serbian Information Ministry
today.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the government had examined at today's
session the findings of the Justice Ministry, at the order of
Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic, to the effect that the truth
be established regarding the municipal elections in Nis and the
public duly informed.
</P>
<P>
The Justice Ministry had admitted that the opposition coalition
Zajedno had won 37 seats, the ruling Socialist Party of Serbia 32
and the Serbian Radical Party one seat in the municipal assembly
of Nis, the second largest city located in southern Serbia, it
said.
</P>
<P>
The statement, released by the official Tanjug news agency,
said the conditions for determining the final results in all the
election precincts were met, following procedures by election
organs and competent courts.
</P>
<P>
The government ordered the Justice Ministry to take measures to
establish accountability for those responsible for the
irregularities.
</P>
<P>
This is apparently a concession made by the government after
the Zajedno coalition staged daily demonstrations in the center of
Belgrade over the past 50 days to protest against the annulment of
the local election results. Zajedno claimed it had won 15 out of
18 largest cities in Serbia in the November 17 elections for local
assemblies and demanded the election results be reinstated.
</P>
<P>
A delegation of the Organization for Security and Cooperation
in Europe which visited Belgrade for a fact-finding mission
confirmed the opposition's victory in the local elections.
</P>
<P>
The government's statement said the above measure showed that
"problems, omissions, errors and abuses can be resolved
efficiently only in the institutions of the system," because
everything that had been resolved regarding the local elections
had been done so in legal institutions, not in the street.
</P>
<P>
"Whatever irregularities are made, regardless of protests, will
be set right in line with regulations and in legal institutions,"
said the statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
